<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
<bibRefCitation author="Perret, J-L" journalOrPublisher="Abteilung fuer Systematik, Oekologie und Geographie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="289 - 464" refId="B151" refString="Perret, J-L, 1966. Les amphibiens du Cameroun. Zoologische Jahrbuecher. Abteilung fuer Systematik, Oekologie und Geographie 93: 289 - 464" title="Les amphibiens du Cameroun. Zoologische Jahrbuecher." volume="93" year="1966">Perret (1966</bibRefCitation>
: 408) considered the type material of 
<taxonomicName class="Amphibia" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. acutirostris" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutirostris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">H. acutirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lost and designated MHNG 965.12 as neotype. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer, AM" editor="Bauer, AM" journalOrPublisher="C. H. Peters (1815 - 1883). Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="39 - 81" refId="B21" refString="Bauer, AM, Guenther, R, Klipfel, M, 1995. Synopsis of taxa. In: Bauer, AM, Guenther, R, Klipfel, M, Eds., Herpetological Contributions of W. C.H. Peters (1815-1883). Society for the Study of Amphibians and Reptiles, Oxford: 39 - 81" title="Synopsis of taxa." volumeTitle="Herpetological Contributions of W." year="1995">Bauer et al. (1995</bibRefCitation>
: 43) could only locate one of the two syntypes. The type locality was corrected to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Douala”">&quot;Douala&quot;</normalizedToken>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fretey, T" journalOrPublisher="Alytes" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="11 - 26" refId="B59" refString="Fretey, T, Dubois, A, Ohler, A, 2014. The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina. Alytes 30: 11 - 26" title="The status of the nomen Hyperolius guttatus Peters, 1875 (Amphibia: Anura) and allied nomina." volume="30" year="2014">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Frétey">Fretey</normalizedToken>
et al. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
; for further information see also remarks on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1875" class="Reptilia" family="Hyperoliidae" genus="Hyperolius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperolius guttatus" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="407">Hyperolius guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
The German explorer, zoologist and anatomist Buchholz went to Equatorial Africa from 1872 to 1875. He was accompanied by the Berlin ornithologist Georg Anton Eugen Reichenow and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Reichenow’s">Reichenow's</normalizedToken>
friend, fellow student and zoologist Wilhelm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lühder">Luehder</normalizedToken>
. On 1 June 1872 they set off from Bremerhaven to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Akkrá">&quot;Akkra</normalizedToken>
on the Gold Coast&quot; [Accra, Ghana], which they reached on 29 July 1872. The first collecting tours took place in the surroundings of Accra and Aburi (29 July to 16 October 1872). On 16 October they left Accra for 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Camaroons”">&quot;Camaroons&quot;</normalizedToken>
[today part of present day Douala city] where they stayed until 2 November. Then they travelled to Bimbia, Victoria and Bonjonjo (2 November 1872 to 9 December 1873). On 12 March 1873 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lühder">Luehder</normalizedToken>
died of malaria in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Camaroons’">'Camaroons'</normalizedToken>
. Reichenow, also suffering from malaria, returned via Gabon to Germany in April 1873.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
Buchholz was on his own from then on. He travelled between Victoria and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="`Camaroons’">'Camaroons'</normalizedToken>
with intermediate stops on Fernando 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pó">Po</normalizedToken>
to get his collections to Camaroons in early December.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="407">
Thereafter he went to Abo (9 December 1873 to 24 March 1874) and from Mungo via Balong he returned again to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="‘Camaroons’">'Camaroons'</normalizedToken>
(5 April to 11 August 1874). He left 
<normalizedToken originalValue="`Camaroons’">'Camaroons'</normalizedToken>
for a stay in Gabon where he also explored the Rembo River (12 August to 9 November 1874). After his return to the Gabon coast he again explored the area around Mungo and Jenssoki (9 November 1874 to 11 January 1875), and again visited Fernando 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pó">Po</normalizedToken>
, the Gabon coast and the Ogowe (or 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ogooué">Ogooue</normalizedToken>
) River (11 January to 31 August 1875). On 3 September he started from Gabon on his way back to Greifswald where he arrived during the beginning of November 1875 (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" author="Reichenow, A" journalOrPublisher="Journal fuer Ornithologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="353 - 388" refId="B174" refString="Reichenow, A, 1874. Zur Vogelfauna Westafrika's. Ergebnisse einer Reise nach Guinea. Journal fuer Ornithologie 22 (128): 353 - 388, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" title="Zur Vogelfauna Westafrika's. Ergebnisse einer Reise nach Guinea." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02004082" volume="22" year="1874">Reichenow 1874</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Heinersdorff, C" journalOrPublisher="Edition Doerfler, Nebel Verlag, Utting" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B90" refString="Heinersdorff, C, 1880. Reinhold Buchholz' Reisen in West-Afrika nach seinen hinterlassenen Tagebuechern und Briefen nebst einem Lebensabriss des Verstorbenen. F. A. Brockhaus, Leipzig, [viii + (2)] 263 pp. [map.]" title="Reinhold Buchholz' Reisen in West-Afrika nach seinen hinterlassenen Tagebuechern und Briefen nebst einem Lebensabriss des Verstorbenen. F. A. Brockhaus, Leipzig, [viii + (2)] 263 pp. [map.]" year="1880">Heinersdorff 1880</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weidmann, C" journalOrPublisher="Bernhard Noehring, Luebeck, (9)" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" refId="B224" refString="Weidmann, C, 1894. Deutsche Maenner in Afrika - Lexicon der hervorragendsten deutschen Afrika-Forscher, Missionare etc. Bernhard Noehring, Luebeck, (9)" title="Deutsche Maenner in Afrika - Lexicon der hervorragendsten deutschen Afrika-Forscher, Missionare etc." year="1894">Weidmann 1894</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" author="Stresemann, E" journalOrPublisher="Journal fuer Ornithologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="111 - 120" refId="B208" refString="Stresemann, E, 1943. Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847-6. VII. 1941. Journal fuer Ornithologie 91 (1): 111 - 120, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" title="Anton Reichenow. 1. VIII. 1847 - 6. VII. 1941." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF01967662" volume="91" year="1943">Stresemann 1943</bibRefCitation>
). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Buchholz’">Buchholz'</normalizedToken>
collections went to the zoological museums in Greifswald and Berlin and his herpetological material has been described by Wilhelm C. H. Peters (
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W [CH]" journalOrPublisher="Monatsberichte der Koeniglichen Preussische Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="196 - 212" refId="B157" refString="Peters, W[CH], 1875. Ueber die von Hrn. Professor Dr. R. Buchholz in Westafrika gesammelten Amphibien. Monatsberichte der Koeniglichen Preussische Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin 1875: 196 - 212" title="Ueber die von Hrn. Professor Dr. R. Buchholz in Westafrika gesammelten Amphibien." volume="1875" year="1875">Peters 1875</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W [CH]" journalOrPublisher="Monatsberichte der Koeniglichen Preussische Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="407" pagination="117 - 123" refId="B158" refString="Peters, W[CH], 1876. Eine zweite Mittheilung ueber die von Hrn. Professor Dr. R. Buchholz in Westafrica gesammelten Amphibien. Monatsberichte der Koeniglichen Preussische Akademie der Wissenschaften zu Berlin 1876: 117 - 123" title="Eine zweite Mittheilung ueber die von Hrn. Professor Dr. R. Buchholz in Westafrica gesammelten Amphibien." volume="1876" year="1876">1876</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
